<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900815-0019</DOCNO><DOCID>900815-0019.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Southwest Gas Corp.:   Net Loss of $6.1 Million   Reported for 2nd Quarter</HL><DATE>08/15/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   SWX</CO><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   Southwest Gas Corp. posted a second-quarter net loss of$6.1 million, or 33 cents a share, compared with net incomeof $388,000, or less that one cent a share, a year ago.   Revenue fell 6.4% to $171.7 million from $183.4 million.</LP><TEXT>   The Las Vegas, Nev.-based natural gas and financialservices concern attributed the net loss to increased costsassociated with providing gas service to the company'sgrowing customer base; increased depreciation expense andgeneral taxes relating to natural gas pipe replacementprograms in Arizona; and costs for expanding and upgradingfacilities.   Gas operations had a loss of $8.5 million for the quarter,compared with a loss of $3.1 million a year ago. Operatingearnings from the company's financial services subsidiary,PriMerit Bank, fell to $3.4 million in the quarter from $4.5million a year ago, beacuse of a drop in real estatedevelopment income and increased general and administrativeexpenses due to the expansion of PriMerit's branch network inNevada and Arizona. This was offset by improved net interestmargins, the company said.   For the six months, net income fell 33% to $15.3 million,or 74 cents a share, from $22.9 million, or $1.16 a share.Revenue rose less than one percent to $445.3 million from$441.7 million.</TEXT></DOC>